WINDOW(TABS) press the prefix keys before typing any of the following commands:

(1) c <create window>
(2) w <list windows>
(3) n <next window>
(4) p <previous window>
(5) , <name window>
(6) & <kill window>


PANES(SPLITS) press the prefix keys before typing any of the following commands

(1) x <kill pane>
(2) : resize-pane -D <resizes the current pane downwards>
(3) : resize-pane -U <resizes the current pane upwards>
(4) : resize-pane -L <resizes the current pane leftwards>
(5) : resize-pane -R <resizes the current pane rightwards>


DISABLE TMUX STATUS BAR:

tmux set -g status off

